08/07/2010
THE HAGUE, The Netherlands -- The UN war crimes tribunal is investigating media allegations that Serb Radical Party leader Vojislav Seselj has ordered the assassination of Serbian Progressive Party leader Tomislav Nikolic. Seselj is currently on trial at The Hague. Tribunal spokesperson Nerma Jelacic told journalists Wednesday (July 7th) that the investigation so far has found no evidence to support the allegations. Seselj has dismissed them as "lies and slander". (B92, Beta, RTS, Radio Free Europe - 07/07/10)
